.TH "LIGHTNING-PEER-ALIAS" 1 "May 2026" "lightning 0.6.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-peer-alias \- look up a peer's alias and colour from gossip
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning peer-alias
.I peer_id
.SH DESCRIPTION
Calls
.B lightning-cli listnodes
with the given
.I peer_id
and returns the alias and colour announced in gossip.
Returns
.B {"error":"not_found"}
if the node is not in the local gossip graph.
.PP
Output:
.nf
{"peer_id":..., "alias":..., "color":...}
.fi
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Always.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lightning-peer-info (1),
.BR lightning-node-gossip (1)
